00:08:59.960 --> 00:09:03.390
So what happened on a fault?

00:09:03.390 --> 00:09:06.150
We think about
earthquake cycles,

00:09:06.150 --> 00:09:08.720
because an earthquake
happens, it heals,

00:09:08.720 --> 00:09:10.770
it's in between
cycles and hit again

00:09:10.770 --> 00:09:12.750
and it's supposed
to be periodic.

00:09:12.750 --> 00:09:15.060
Scientists today do not
really like the word cycle

00:09:15.060 --> 00:09:20.630
because of this irregularity
in some of the fault systems.

00:09:20.630 --> 00:09:23.220
But I'd like to just
emphasize that it's just

00:09:23.220 --> 00:09:25.860
a very, if we think about
it, a very simple model.

00:09:25.860 --> 00:09:27.360
You can think about
this model where

00:09:27.360 --> 00:09:30.600
you have a spring in a handle.

00:09:30.600 --> 00:09:34.360
You have a sure phase that could
be rough or smooth as you wish.

00:09:34.360 --> 00:09:37.100
And then you have a
block, and you pull it.

00:09:37.100 --> 00:09:40.770
So that if you have elasticity
in your string here,

00:09:40.770 --> 00:09:42.480
the block is not
going to move as you

00:09:42.480 --> 00:09:47.430
pull until it's too
tensed, and then the block

00:09:47.430 --> 00:09:49.680
will slide it toward you.

00:09:49.680 --> 00:09:52.020
And so this effect of
increasing the stress

00:09:52.020 --> 00:09:55.260
loading on the
string, and then slip,

00:09:55.260 --> 00:09:58.800
and it sticks, and it slips,
and so on and so forth,

00:09:58.800 --> 00:10:03.056
is the fundamental view
of earthquake cycle,

00:10:03.056 --> 00:10:04.680
where you increase
the force the plates

00:10:04.680 --> 00:10:09.320
are moving at a somewhat regular
pace and then it's locked.

00:10:09.320 --> 00:10:11.320
It sticks, and then
[INAUDIBLE] to an earthquake

00:10:11.320 --> 00:10:12.850
and so on and so forth.

00:10:12.850 --> 00:10:15.450
So if we model
forces in the earth,

00:10:15.450 --> 00:10:18.570
you can say it's a constant
forcing, constant slip

00:10:18.570 --> 00:10:22.510
constant forcing, constant
slip, this is the ideal case.

00:10:22.510 --> 00:10:24.370
We have in the United
States one fault

00:10:24.370 --> 00:10:28.230
that seem to behave like this.

00:10:28.230 --> 00:10:31.410
It's in San Andreas fault
in the Parkfield area

00:10:31.410 --> 00:10:33.510
and it was so
regular in the past.

00:10:33.510 --> 00:10:36.630
These are years of occurrence
of these earthquakes.

00:10:36.630 --> 00:10:39.861
Every 20 plus years there
was a little magnitude 6

00:10:39.861 --> 00:10:42.360
that would occur on this fault.
So these are the earthquakes

00:10:42.360 --> 00:10:46.680
series and you can look at
number of earthquakes and time.

00:10:46.680 --> 00:10:48.660
You draw a line and
you predict when

00:10:48.660 --> 00:10:50.820
the next earthquake will go.

00:10:50.820 --> 00:10:54.940
So the prediction was that
