00:10:56.590 --> 00:10:58.800
So the USGS deployed
a lot of resources

00:10:58.800 --> 00:11:01.290
around Parkfield to
instrument the fault

00:11:01.290 --> 00:11:04.740
and to capture the full cycle.

00:11:04.740 --> 00:11:06.547
But the earthquake
did not happen.

00:11:06.547 --> 00:11:08.130
And I think a lot
of the seismologists

00:11:08.130 --> 00:11:11.370
completely lost faith
because it took many more

00:11:11.370 --> 00:11:14.530
years for the earthquake
to actually occur.

00:11:14.530 --> 00:11:19.800
And so I think when big events
like this, either like Tohoku

00:11:19.800 --> 00:11:22.440
or all these events where we
don't expect them to happen,

00:11:22.440 --> 00:11:25.920
it's very hard for
seismologists to react.

00:11:25.920 --> 00:11:29.340
And so I think because of
that, a lot of the seismology

00:11:29.340 --> 00:11:31.920
has been going away
from prediction.

00:11:31.920 --> 00:11:35.250
It was all about prediction
before, this has failed,

00:11:35.250 --> 00:11:38.700
let's move on and not
predict earthquake any more.

00:11:38.700 --> 00:11:40.620
So let's think about
this time theory

00:11:40.620 --> 00:11:42.210
that I was just drawing you.

00:11:42.210 --> 00:11:45.330
We have the earthquake
at time zero,

00:11:45.330 --> 00:11:48.600
we have what happens before
or in between earthquakes,

00:11:48.600 --> 00:11:50.980
and then we have
what happens after.

00:11:50.980 --> 00:11:53.780
So here, I'm showing you
that between years to months

00:11:53.780 --> 00:11:55.860
to second before
the earthquake, this

00:11:55.860 --> 00:11:58.890
is the phase that we
call a nucleation phase.

00:11:58.890 --> 00:12:01.290
We are at the end of
the earthquake cycle,

00:12:01.290 --> 00:12:04.770
something is happening, we
will have an earthquake.

00:12:04.770 --> 00:12:08.040
We just don't know when t=0 is.

00:12:08.040 --> 00:12:11.299
What happens after is
the earthquake ruptures.

00:12:11.299 --> 00:12:12.840
It's not and
[SNAPS FINGERS] instant.

00:12:12.840 --> 00:12:15.550
It's not a snap like
this, it takes some time.

00:12:15.550 --> 00:12:19.147
So we have a few seconds to
tens of seconds, during which

00:12:19.147 --> 00:12:21.480
and after which all the
shaking, the ground motion goes,

00:12:21.480 --> 00:12:23.920
and that's what
destroys the building.

00:12:23.920 --> 00:12:27.420
So the prediction of
earthquakes within years,

00:12:27.420 --> 00:12:30.910
I'm a little bit
skeptical today.

00:12:30.910 --> 00:12:32.580
And I would say that
probably we may not

00:12:32.580 --> 00:12:35.640
be able to do that
anytime soon, mostly

00:12:35.640 --> 00:12:39.120
because we do have many
years in our records.

