00:27:41.100 --> 00:27:42.790
Another example.

00:27:42.790 --> 00:27:45.060
We got thousands and thousands
of these functions that

00:27:45.060 --> 00:27:50.770
look like earthquakes, but
really they vary a lot.

00:27:50.770 --> 00:27:54.750
So part of the
research that I started

00:27:54.750 --> 00:27:59.760
doing this summer with a really,
really good team of students,

00:27:59.760 --> 00:28:02.070
I was so fortunate.

00:28:02.070 --> 00:28:03.570
I really love
working with students

00:28:03.570 --> 00:28:07.080
who have no a priori on
seismology whatsoever

00:28:07.080 --> 00:28:08.820
and start asking
these questions that

00:28:08.820 --> 00:28:11.480
are so fundamental,
