00:28:24.370 --> 00:28:27.780
In actually found a
really interesting pattern

00:28:27.780 --> 00:28:30.060
in the complexity
of earthquakes.

00:28:30.060 --> 00:28:33.210
So it's is no longer about
let's simplify everything

00:28:33.210 --> 00:28:35.070
into averaging everything.

00:28:35.070 --> 00:28:37.530
He said let's look
at this complexity,

00:28:37.530 --> 00:28:40.470
embrace it and find patterns.

00:28:40.470 --> 00:28:43.180
And so I will
summarize it in such.

00:28:43.180 --> 00:28:45.060
We have an earthquake here.

00:28:45.060 --> 00:28:50.100
It's a big earthquake, probably
a magnitude 7.5, maybe 8

00:28:50.100 --> 00:28:53.530
given the duration here,
60 second of duration.

00:28:53.530 --> 00:28:55.400
This function could
be like a P wave,

00:28:55.400 --> 00:28:58.170
so you could see that
